
    -Atomic operation:
        An atomic operation, is guaranteed to work on variables without interference from other operations. 
    -Semaphore:
       A variable or abstract data type that controls access to a common resource. A "busy" sign
    -Mutex:
       Mutex is short for mutual exclusion, it is a way to avoid race conditions. To do this, the critical section of a thread, can not
       operate at the same time as the critical section of a concurent thread.
    -Critical section:
      Part of a thread that is dependant on no iterference from concurrent threads.
